cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with improving the performance of graph neural networks (GNNs) through a novel normalization layer. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GNNs are a popular tool in AI research. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with graph data. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GNNs have been used in various computer vision tasks.
